@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Flechino" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher.

                             How to play?

  To play, click on an arrow. If the arrow points towards an arrow
that points in a different direction, both arrows will exchange
their positions and a small square will appear at the initial
position of the clicked arrow, if a square was not already there.

  If the clicked arrow points toward the border of the game board
or toward an arrow that points in the same direction, the clicked
arrow will turn clockwise by 90 degrees.

  The size of the game board can be changed from a 3 by 3 arrow
size up to an 8 by 8 arrow size. Click on the '+' or '-' symbols
displayed under the game board (or by using the '+' or '-' keys of
the keyboard) to change the game board size.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

